💻 Tech Stack

Frontend Technologies

React.js

React.js is used to build a dynamic and responsive user interface. Its component-based architecture allows different sections of the application, such as the dashboard, task manager, mood tracker, and analytics page, to be developed and maintained efficiently.

HTML5

HTML5 provides the fundamental structure of the application. It is used to organize content, forms, navigation menus, and interactive elements throughout the platform.

CSS3

CSS3 is responsible for the visual design of the application. It enables responsive layouts, smooth animations, custom themes, and the aesthetic study environments such as the Library, Coffee Shop, and Japanese Café backgrounds.

JavaScript

JavaScript powers the interactive functionality of the platform, including task management, Pomodoro timers, reward calculations, mood tracking, and real-time user interactions.


---

Backend Technologies

Node.js

Node.js serves as the backend runtime environment, handling application logic, user requests, data processing, and communication between the frontend and database.

Express.js

Express.js is used to create RESTful APIs that manage user authentication, task data, study analytics, friend connections, and reward system operations.


---

Database

MongoDB

MongoDB is used as the primary database for storing and managing user information, including profiles, tasks, study history, mood records, review habits, rewards, and analytics data. Its flexible document-based structure makes it suitable for handling diverse user-generated data.


---

Authentication and Security

Firebase Authentication

Firebase Authentication provides secure user registration and login functionality. It supports email-based authentication and ensures that user data remains protected through secure authentication mechanisms.


---

Adaptive Learning Engine

Custom Recommendation System

A custom-built adaptive learning engine analyzes user behavior, including:

Attention span

Task completion patterns

Revision frequency

Mistake trends

Daily mood tracking


Based on these factors, the system generates personalized study recommendations, adaptive Pomodoro schedules, and revision suggestions to improve learning efficiency.


---

Analytics System

Performance Tracking Module

The analytics module collects and processes study-related data to generate insights such as:

Daily study time

Productivity trends

Focus performance

Revision consistency

Goal completion rates


These insights help students understand their learning habits and make informed improvements.


---

Deployment and Hosting

Vercel / Netlify

Used for deploying and hosting the frontend application, ensuring fast loading times, scalability, and reliable accessibility.

Render / Railway

Used for backend deployment and API hosting, providing stable server performance and database connectivity.


---

Development Tools

Git

Git is used for version control, enabling efficient tracking of code changes and collaborative development.

GitHub

GitHub serves as the central repository for source code management, project collaboration, documentation, issue tracking, and deployment integration.


---

Together, these technologies create a scalable, secure, and intelligent platform that delivers personalized study planning, adaptive learning recommendations, productivity tracking, and an engaging gamified experience for students through My Matcha Study Planner. 🍵📚🚀
